<item>
            <title>[FLINK-21660] CREATE TABLE LIKE cannot reference tables in HiveCatalog</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/FLINK-21660</link>
                <project id="12315522" key="FLINK">Flink</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;create a table like with a hive catalog table&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#cc7832&quot;&gt;CREATE TABLE &lt;/font&gt;temp_order&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;font color=&quot;#cc7832&quot;&gt;WITH &lt;/font&gt;(&lt;br/&gt;
 &lt;font color=&quot;#6a8759&quot;&gt;&apos;properties.group.id&apos; &lt;/font&gt;= &lt;font color=&quot;#6a8759&quot;&gt;&apos;test1&apos;&lt;/font&gt;&lt;font color=&quot;#cc7832&quot;&gt;,&lt;/font&gt; &lt;font color=&quot;#6a8759&quot;&gt;&apos;properties.bootstrap.servers&apos; &lt;/font&gt;= &lt;font color=&quot;#6a8759&quot;&gt;&apos;kafka.address&apos;&lt;/font&gt;)&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;font color=&quot;#cc7832&quot;&gt;LIKE &lt;/font&gt;hive.ods.flink_order&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It has a error, log is :&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Exception in thread &quot;main&quot; org.apache.flink.table.api.ValidationException: Unable to create a source for reading table &apos;default_catalog.default_database.test_taos_customer_agent_cinema&apos;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Table options are:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&apos;connector&apos;=&apos;upsert-kafka&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
&apos;is_generic&apos;=&apos;true&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
&apos;key.format&apos;=&apos;json&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
&apos;properties.bootstrap.servers&apos;=&apos;kafka.address&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
&apos;properties.group.id&apos;=&apos;test1&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
&apos;topic&apos;=&apos;topic1&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
&apos;value.format&apos;=&apos;json&apos;&lt;br/&gt;
...&lt;br/&gt;
Caused by: org.apache.flink.table.api.ValidationException: Unsupported options found for connector &apos;upsert-kafka&apos;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Unsupported options:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;is_generic&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;the &#8217;is_generic&#8216; option is&#160; added by hive catalog,&#160; but&#160; `kafka` connector&#160; does not support this&#160; option.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
